📢The Vita Coco Company is officially a Certified B Corporation! In a (coco)nutshell, this means that we prioritize treating people, the planet, and coconuts properly, from source to shelf, along every step of our business. Our mission is to create more equitable access to natural, better-for-you products, and ya know, make delicious coconut water too. We’re so excited to be in such great company as a B Corp company! 🥥

latestIgtvVideos.title: The Classroom that Built a Village.
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
At Vita Coco we believe that when we invest in education, we can help empower our coconut farming communities. So in 2019, in partnership with our friends at @hopeinabottleph, we built two new classrooms and installed solar panels at COLOT IP School, to support the students that would travel 3-5 hours every week just to learn. Because of the new classrooms, enrollment increased by 220% and 40 families relocated their homes to build a community around the school. In COLOT, education literally powered a new village, and we’re so excited to see it continue to grow.

For every like on this post, we’ll donate $1 towards our new classroom fund (up to $10,000), which will go towards building a second facility that can double as a community center.  #InternationalDayOfEducation

latestIgtvVideos.title: World Coconut Day
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Under normal circumstances, we'd celebrate World Coconut Day with a big ol' party. But because we couldn’t all be together, we mailed our employees green coconuts and asked them to pretend they were passing a coconut to their coworker (we heard it was a thing on Tik Tok) so we could have a fun, trendy piece of content to share.
 
We never expected them to be sitting in kiddie pools, jumping on trampolines, and executing costume changes. So it’s got me thinking I should just have them create our social media content from now on....?
